@startuml
title path — high-level sequence
actor User
participant Discord as "discord.py"
participant Bot as "DiscordBot (src/discord_bot.py)"
participant AsyncRoute as "ed_route_async"
participant Route as "ed_route"
participant BFS as "ed_bfs"
participant Cache as "Ed_Cache (edgis_cache)"
database DB as "TinyDB (data/*.db)"
participant EDGIS as "EDGIS (external HTTP API)"

User -> Discord: sends `!path <start> <dest>` command
Discord -> Bot: dispatch command handler
Bot -> AsyncRoute: await path(start, dest)
AsyncRoute -> Route: path(start, dest)
Route -> Route: initialize_preloaded_db(preinit_db_filename)
Route -> DB: DB(db_filename) constructor / open
Route -> Cache: Ed_Cache(database)
Route -> BFS: travel(cache.find_system_info, cache.find_system_neighbors, start, dest)
BFS -> Cache: fetch current node info via find_system_info(name)
Cache -> DB: get_system(name)
alt cached
    DB --> Cache: return system_info
else not cached
    Cache -> EDGIS: GET /coords?q=<name>
    EDGIS --> Cache: JSON system_info
    Cache -> DB: insert_system(system_info)
end
BFS -> Cache: find_system_neighbors(system_info)
Cache -> DB: get_system(system_name)
alt neighbors cached
    DB --> Cache: return neighbors
else neighbors not cached
    Cache -> EDGIS: GET /neighbors?x=...&y=...&z=...
    EDGIS --> Cache: neighbors list
    Cache -> DB: add_neighbors(system_info, neighbors)
end
BFS -> BFS: enqueue neighbor paths until destination found or max reached
BFS --> Route: return route (list of system names)
Route --> AsyncRoute: return route
AsyncRoute --> Bot: route
Bot -> Discord: ctx.send("Route from <start> to <dest>: ...")
@enduml
